  ],
  "text": "The CSS style-to-paint rendering pipeline in Chromium's Blink engine involves four key stages:\n\n1. StyleResolver (third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.cc): Resolves computed styles for DOM elements by matching CSS rules, cascading, and inheriting values to produce the final ComputedStyle for each element.\n\n2. LayoutObject (third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.cc): The base class for the layout tree. After styles are resolved, LayoutObject subclasses compute geometry (position, size, etc.) for each element. A style change triggers layout invalidation which causes LayoutObject::UpdateLayout() to recompute positions.\n\n3. PaintLayer (third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.cc): The painting layer abstraction, corresponding to elements that form stacking contexts or compositing layers. PaintLayer manages the painting order and compositing decisions after layout.\n\n4. PaintController / DisplayItemList (third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.cc and third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.cc): The display list infrastructure that records paint operations. PaintController manages the display item list and caching; DisplayItemList stores the sequence of paint commands that are ultimately rasterized to produce pixels."
}

